---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Fractional CRO Services",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Glen Swindell",
    "jobTitle": "Fractional Chief Revenue Officer"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Plano TX", "Dallas TX", "DFW", "United States"],
  "description": "Fractional Chief Revenue Officer services for B2B SaaS and fintech companies. 10+ years revenue leadership. Past clients include Verifone and Bread Financial."
};
---

<Base
  title="Fractional CRO for B2B SaaS & Fintech | OrangeCore Group | Plano, TX"
  description="Glen Swindell is a fractional Chief Revenue Officer serving B2B SaaS and fintech companies. 10+ years revenue leadership. Past clients include Verifone and Bread Financial."
  schema={schema}
>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hc1"></div><div class="hc2"></div>
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="eyebrow hero-ey">Fractional CRO · Plano, TX & Remote</div>
      <h1>Fractional Chief Revenue Officer for B2B SaaS and Fintech Companies</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Glen Swindell brings 10+ years of revenue leadership to companies that need CRO-level thinking without the full-time price tag. Fintech and payments background. Army veteran discipline. Productized approach — so you know exactly what you're getting.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Book a discovery call</a>
        <a href="/services/" class="btn-hero-outline">See Operate tier — $7,500/mo</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="what-section fade-in">
        <div class="section-header">
          <p class="eyebrow">What a fractional CRO actually does</p>
          <h2>Not strategy decks. Actual revenue work.</h2>
          <p>The title sounds big. The day-to-day is concrete. Here's what changes when Glen is in the room.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="what-grid">
          <div class="what-card">
            <h3>Pipeline & Forecast</h3>
            <p>Monthly pipeline reviews with leadership. Stage-weighted forecasting that's actually defensible. Reps held to a process, not a gut feeling.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-card">
            <h3>Sales Playbook</h3>
            <p>Talk tracks, objection handling, discovery frameworks — built for your specific ICP. Not a template from a generic sales consulting firm that's never touched your vertical.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-card">
            <h3>RevOps & CRM</h3>
            <p>HubSpot, Salesforce, or Pipedrive configured to match your actual sales motion. Data you can trust. Dashboards leadership will actually open.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-card">
            <h3>Go-to-Market Alignment</h3>
            <p>Marketing and sales working off the same definition of a qualified lead. Handoff process documented. No more "marketing sends us garbage" conversations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-card">
            <h3>Team Coaching</h3>
            <p>Bi-weekly coaching sessions with the sales team. Pattern recognition from working across B2B SaaS, fintech, and payments — not generic sales coaching.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="what-card">
            <h3>Board & Investor Prep</h3>
            <p>Revenue narrative, pipeline story, forecast model — built for the board meeting or fundraise conversation, not assembled the night before.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="ai-note">Every engagement is AI-augmented. Deliverables are more thorough, documentation is more complete, and the turnaround is faster — without cutting corners on the thinking behind it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="signals-section fade-in">
        <div class="signals-inner">
          <div class="signals-text">
            <p class="eyebrow">When to hire one</p>
            <h2>Five signals it's time to bring in a fractional CRO.</h2>
            <p>Most companies wait too long. If you're recognizing more than two of these, it's probably time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="signals-list">
            <div class="signal-item">
              <span class="signal-num">01</span>
              <div>
                <p class="signal-title">Revenue is inconsistent — and nobody knows why</p>
                <p class="signal-desc">Good quarter, bad quarter, no real explanation for either. That's a process problem, not a market problem.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="signal-item">
              <span class="signal-num">02</span>
              <div>
                <p class="signal-title">The CEO is still running revenue</p>
                <p class="signal-desc">At some point this stops scaling. If the founder is still the de facto CRO, something needs to change before the next growth phase.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="signal-item">
              <span class="signal-num">03</span>
              <div>
                <p class="signal-title">You just hired a sales team</p>
                <p class="signal-desc">Reps without a playbook, process, or pipeline structure will figure it out on their own — and the results will be variable at best.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="signal-item">
              <span class="signal-num">04</span>
              <div>
                <p class="signal-title">You're prepping for a Series A or B</p>
                <p class="signal-desc">Investors want to see a repeatable revenue motion. If your pipeline and forecast aren't board-ready, that conversation is going to be uncomfortable.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="signal-item">
              <span class="signal-num">05</span>
              <div>
                <p class="signal-title">A full-time CRO isn't in the budget yet</p>
                <p class="signal-desc">A qualified CRO runs $200K–$300K in salary. Fractional gives you the thinking and the output at a fraction of that cost — with defined scope, not an open-ended engagement.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="diff-section fade-in">
        <p class="eyebrow">What makes Glen different</p>
        <h2>Depth, not breadth.</h2>
        <div class="diff-grid">
          <div class="diff-item">
            <h3>Payments & Fintech</h3>
            <p>Interchange economics, tokenization, BNPL infrastructure, enterprise procurement in financial services — this isn't a talking point. Past clients include Verifone and Bread Financial. If your buyers include bank risk committees or enterprise procurement teams in regulated industries, that background matters.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-item">
            <h3>Army Veteran</h3>
            <p>8 years in the U.S. Army (2010–2018). Discipline, systems thinking, people-first leadership — those translate directly to how revenue operations runs. Processes get documented. Accountability is real. Work gets done.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-item">
            <h3>Productized, Not Open-Ended</h3>
            <p>Most fractional consultants charge hourly and let scope expand. Every OrangeCore engagement has defined deliverables, defined timelines, and a defined end. You know exactly what you're getting before anything starts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="diff-item">
            <h3>Based in Plano, TX</h3>
            <p>Local to the DFW market. Available for in-person work when it matters. National clients served remotely — same deliverables, same accountability, same timeline regardless of geography.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="wont-section fade-in">
        <h2>What you won't get.</h2>
        <p class="wont-sub">Worth being direct about this.</p>
        <div class="wont-grid">
          <div class="wont-item"><span>—</span><span>Day-to-day sales management. That's a hire, not a consultant. Glen operates at the strategy and process layer.</span></div>
          <div class="wont-item"><span>—</span><span>Open-ended retainers with no defined output. Engage tires of those fast. So does every good fractional.</span></div>
          <div class="wont-item"><span>—</span><span>Vague "strategic guidance." Every engagement produces specific, documented deliverables.</span></div>
          <div class="wont-item"><span>—</span><span>A generalist who Googles your industry. B2B SaaS and fintech are the focus — not general B2B, not consumer, not e-commerce.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-block fade-in">
        <div class="pricing-block-inner">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">The Operate Tier</p>
            <h2>Fractional CRO engagement starts at $7,500/mo.</h2>
            <p>3-month minimum. Deliverables defined at kickoff — not left open-ended. Monthly pipeline review, one major deliverable per month, bi-weekly coaching, async Slack access.</p>
            <p style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:14px;color:#9A9590;">This is the primary vehicle for fractional CRO work. For a one-time project (playbook, GTM strategy, board prep), see the Build tier or Add-ons on the services page.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-cta-col">
            <div class="price-display">
              <span class="price-main">$7,500</span>
              <span class="price-suffix">/mo</span>
            </div>
            <p class="price-sub">3-month minimum</p>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary" style="display:block;text-align:center;margin-top:1rem;">Book a discovery call</a>
            <a href="/services/" class="btn-outline" style="display:block;text-align:center;margin-top:0.75rem;">Full pricing →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section fade-in">
        <div class="section-header">
          <p class="eyebrow">Common questions</p>
          <h2>Fractional CRO questions we hear a lot.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <p class="faq-q">What's the difference between a fractional CRO and a sales consultant?</p>
            <p class="faq-a">A sales consultant typically comes in for a specific project — a playbook, a training, a process doc. A fractional CRO operates at the strategic level on an ongoing basis: pipeline, forecast, team coaching, GTM alignment, board prep. Different scope, different relationship.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <p class="faq-q">How long until we see results?</p>
            <p class="faq-a">Depends on what's broken. Pipeline clarity and CRM cleanup show results in weeks. Consistent revenue improvement takes a quarter to show up in the numbers. Anyone promising faster than that is selling you something.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <p class="faq-q">Do you work with companies outside DFW?</p>
            <p class="faq-a">Yes — most clients are remote. Based in Plano, TX and available for in-person meetings in the DFW area, but the work doesn't require it. Same deliverables, same accountability, same timeline regardless of location.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <p class="faq-q">What CRMs do you work with?</p>
            <p class="faq-a">HubSpot is the primary platform — it's where most of the hands-on buildout work happens. Also have experience in Salesforce and Pipedrive. If you're on something else, let's talk about it during discovery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="footer-cta-banner fade-in">
        <p class="eyebrow">Plano, TX · Serving DFW and national clients</p>
        <h2>Think this might be the right fit?</h2>
        <p>30 minutes. We'll figure out together if a fractional CRO engagement makes sense — and if it doesn't, you'll hear that too.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Book a discovery call</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
.hero{background:var(--charcoal);padding:5rem 0 4rem;position:relative;overflow:hidden;text-align:center;}
.hc1,.hc2{position:absolute;border-radius:50%;background:var(--orange);pointer-events:none;}
.hc1{width:300px;height:300px;top:-60px;right:-60px;opacity:0.07;}
.hc2{width:200px;height:200px;bottom:-60px;left:-40px;opacity:0.04;}
.hero-inner{position:relative;z-index:1;}
.hero-ey{color:var(--orange);border:1px solid rgba(232,97,10,0.4);padding:4px 14px;border-radius:2px;}
.hero h1{font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4.5vw,3rem);font-weight:700;color:#fff;line-height:1.15;letter-spacing:-0.03em;max-width:780px;margin:1rem auto 1.25rem;}
.hero-sub{font-size:16px;color:#9A9590;max-width:620px;margin:0 auto 2.5rem;font-weight:300;line-height:1.75;}
.hero-actions{display:flex;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;}
.btn-hero-outline{display:inline-block;background:transparent;color:#C8C4BF;padding:12px 28px;border-radius:4px;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;border:1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);transition:border-color var(--transition-fast),color var(--transition-fast);}
.btn-hero-outline:hover{border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4);color:#fff;}
.what-section{margin-bottom:5rem;}
.what-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1.25rem;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;}
.what-card{background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:1.5rem;}
.what-card h3{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:0.5rem;}
.what-card p{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.6;}
.ai-note{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--charcoal);background:var(--orange-light);border:1px solid var(--orange-mid);border-radius:6px;padding:1rem 1.25rem;line-height:1.6;}
.signals-section{background:var(--charcoal);border-radius:8px;padding:3rem;margin-bottom:5rem;}
.signals-inner{}
.signals-text{margin-bottom:2.5rem;}
.signals-text .eyebrow{color:var(--orange);}
.signals-text h2{color:#fff;font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2rem);margin:0.5rem 0 0.75rem;}
.signals-text p{font-size:15px;color:#6E6A65;line-height:1.7;}
.signals-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;}
.signal-item{display:flex;gap:1.5rem;padding:1.25rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);align-items:flex-start;}
.signal-item:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
.signal-num{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--orange);opacity:0.5;flex-shrink:0;min-width:32px;}
.signal-title{font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:#E8E4DF;margin-bottom:0.3rem;}
.signal-desc{font-size:13px;color:#6E6A65;line-height:1.6;}
.diff-section{margin-bottom:5rem;}
.diff-section h2{font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2rem);margin:0.5rem 0 2rem;}
.diff-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1.5rem 3rem;}
.diff-item h3{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:0.5rem;}
.diff-item p{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.65;}
.wont-section{background:var(--warm-gray);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:2.5rem;margin-bottom:4rem;}
.wont-section h2{font-size:clamp(1.3rem,2.5vw,1.7rem);margin-bottom:0.4rem;}
.wont-sub{font-size:14px;color:var(--mid-gray);margin-bottom:1.5rem;}
.wont-grid{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem;}
.wont-item{display:flex;gap:12px;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--mid-gray);line-height:1.5;}
.wont-item span:first-child{color:#B0ACA7;flex-shrink:0;}
.pricing-block{background:var(--charcoal);border-radius:8px;padding:3rem;margin-bottom:4rem;}
.pricing-block-inner{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr auto;gap:3rem;align-items:center;}
.pricing-block .eyebrow{color:var(--orange);}
.pricing-block h2{color:#fff;font-size:clamp(1.3rem,2.5vw,1.8rem);margin:0.5rem 0 1rem;}
.pricing-block p{font-size:14.5px;color:#9A9590;line-height:1.7;}
.pricing-cta-col{text-align:center;min-width:180px;}
.price-display{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:4px;justify-content:center;}
.price-main{font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:2.4rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;}
.price-suffix{font-size:1.1rem;color:#6E6A65;}
.price-sub{font-size:12px;color:#6E6A65;margin-top:4px;}
.faq-section{margin-bottom:4rem;}
@media(max-width:768px){.what-grid,.diff-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.pricing-block-inner{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.pricing-cta-col{text-align:left;}.signals-section{padding:2rem;}}
</style>
